article.headline: Wis.-Milwaukee 75, S. Dakota St. 58
article.story: MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Ricky Franklin scored 13 points and Paige Paulsen 12 to help Wisconsin-Milwaukee defeat South Dakota State 75-58 and snap a four-game losing streak Wednesday night. Marcus Skinner, Kevin Massiah and Avery Smith added 10 points apiece for Milwaukee (2-4). The Jackrabbits (0-5) were led by Matt Cadwell with 12 points and Garrett Callahan with 11. The Panthers led 42-32 early in the second half after a basket by Skinner, but the Jackrabbits rallied to tie the score 54-54 on a basket by Jose Frias. Franklin hit a pair of free throws with 6:48 left to snap the tie and ignite a 5-point run that gave Milwaukee a 59-54 lead. The Panthers never lost that lead as the Jackrabbits faded down the stretch in what had been a close game up until then. Skinner's basket with 1.9 seconds left put Milwaukee ahead 35-30 at halftime. The Panthers had led 19-7 at one point after an 8-point run that started with two baskets by Smith. It was the third straight season that Milwaukee has beaten South Dakota State.
